UNITED STATES - Following the success of Bad and Boujee, a number of parody videos have popped up. One of these is Mad and Moody. Bad and Boujee is a song by American hip hop group Migos.It was released as the lead single from their second studio album Culture by Quality Control Entertainment, 300 Entertainment, and Atlantic Records on October 28, 2016.The song, which was produced by Metro Boomin, with co-production by G Koop, features vocals from American rapper Lil Uzi Vert.It reached number one on the Billboard Hot 100, making it the first chart-topping single for both Migos and Lil Uzi Vert."Bad and Boujee" also peaked at number 5 in Canada, making it Migos and Lil Uzi Vert's first charted single in that country.- Additinal Reporting - hotnewhiphop.com.YouTube